Frequently asked questions
--------------------------

### What is PayPal Braintree?

PayPal Braintree is a global payment processing solution that delivers end-to-end checkout experiences for businesses, offering single-touch payments, mobile SDKs, and global currency acceptance for seamless transactions.

### What are the accepted PayPal Braintree payment methods?

PayPal Braintree supports [PayPal](https://www.paypal.com/us/enterprise/payment-processing/accept-paypal) payments, [Venmo](https://www.paypal.com/us/enterprise/payment-processing/accept-venmo) (in the US), credit and debit cards, popular digital wallets like Apple Pay and Google Pay, as well as local payment methods. [Learn more about payment methods](https://www.paypal.com/us/enterprise/payment-methods).

### Where can I log in to my Braintree account?

Using your established Braintree login username and password, you can [access your Braintree Control Panel here](https://www.braintreegateway.com/login). If you have corporate domain credentials, you can [use single sign on to log in](https://id.braintreegateway.com/sso/sessions/new).

### Is PayPal Braintree PCI compliant?

PayPal Braintree is a validated Level 1 PCI DSS compliant service provider and offers a secure checkout experience with ready-built payment interfaces that meet SAQ-A PCI compliance validation requirements. [Learn more about PCI compliance](https://www.paypal.com/us/enterprise/pci-compliance).

### What are the capabilities of the PayPal Braintree Sandbox?

Our [sandbox](https://www.braintreepayments.com/sandbox) lets you test and get a feel for the PayPal Braintree experience before you apply.

*   Try our payment processing platform with no obligation to apply for a PayPal Braintree account
*   Explore the control panel, reporting tools, and features
*   Run sample test transactions, play with subscriptions, and fully test the API

### More ways to use PayPal Braintree

[Case Studies](https://www.paypal.com/us/brc/resources/case-studies?page=1&segment=enterprise) 

[Third-party Integrations](https://www.paypal.com/us/business/platforms-and-marketplaces/solutions)
